Catalyst provides built-in OpenTelemetry support via catalyst-core/otel. Server-side only.

USAGE: Call Otel.init() inside preServerInit() in server/index.js. Guard with an ENABLE flag and skip in development.

import Otel from 'catalyst-core/otel'

export const preServerInit = () => {
  const otelConfig = JSON.parse(process.env.OTEL)
  if (otelConfig.ENABLE && process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'development') {
    Otel.init({
      serviceName: 'my-catalyst-app',
      serviceVersion: process.env.RELEASE_TAG,
      environment: process.env.ENV_NAME,
      traceUrl: otelConfig.ENDPOINT,
      instrumentations: [ new HttpInstrumentation({ ... }) ],
    })
  }
}

CONFIG SHAPE (all optional, defaults shown):
- serviceName: 'catalyst-server'
- serviceVersion: '1.0.0'
- environment: 'development'
- traceUrl: 'http://localhost:4318/v1/traces'
- metricUrl: 'http://localhost:4318/v1/metrics'
- traceHeaders: {}
- metricHeaders: {}
- exportIntervalMillis: 10000
- exportTimeoutMillis: 10000
- instrumentations: [getNodeAutoInstrumentations()] by default

AUTO METRICS: init() automatically collects process_cpu_usage_percent, process_memory_usage_bytes, process_memory_heap_used_bytes, process_memory_heap_total_bytes — no extra config needed.

GRACEFUL SHUTDOWN: SIGTERM and SIGINT handlers registered automatically — sdk.shutdown() is called on process exit.

RETURN VALUE: { sdk, meter } — use meter (OTel Meter instance) to create your own custom metrics via meter.createObservableGauge(), createCounter(), etc.

PEER DEPS: Install @opentelemetry/* packages yourself — not bundled by catalyst-core.
